  "recipeInstructions": [
    {
      "title": "",
      "summary": "Step 1: Prep",
      "text": "### A. Sauté Onion\n* Dice onion *(aim for ~½ cup)*\n* Cook in olive oil on *medium (300–325°F)* until soft/translucent with light golden edges *(6–10 min)*\n* Spread on plate to cool\n\n---\n<br>\n\n### B. Make Panade\n* Mix panko + milk\n* Rest 5–10 minutes\n\n---\n<br>\n\n### C. Mix + Form\n* Combine:\n  * beef\n  * cooled onions\n  * panade\n  * parmesan\n  * garlic powder\n  * oregano\n  * ½ tsp salt\n* Mix gently until just combined\n* Form 12 meatballs\n"
    },
    {
      "title": "",
      "summary": "Step 2: Sear",
      "text": "* Heat pan on *medium-high (375–400°F)*\n* Brown meatballs on all sides *(5–7 min total)*\n* Do not fully cook through\n\n---\n<br>\n\nRemove to a plate.\n"
    },
    {
      "title": "",
      "summary": "Step 3: Simmer (Optional Sauce Step)",
      "text": "* Reduce heat to *medium (300–325°F)*\n* Add sauce\n* Optional: stir in ricotta or cheddar\n* Return meatballs, cover, simmer 15–20 min until 165°F internal\n"
    }
  ],
